Net-MyOpera

A Net::Twitter clone, that works for the My Opera Community,
http://my.opera.com/

Yes, you can update your My Opera status, and the API
is OAuth-enabled. Unlike Net::Twitter, it doesn't depend
on Moose (yet?).

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Net::MyOpera

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Net-MyOpera

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Net-MyOpera

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Net-MyOpera

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Net-MyOpera/


